<script type="text/javascript">

    function getRandomInt(min, max) {
        return Math.floor(Math.random() * (max - min)) + min;
    }    

    var info = [
		["../Images/ItsGood2Give.jpg",
		'<h2>Our Charities: &nbsp;<a href="http://www.itsgood2give.co.uk/">It’s Good 2 Give</a></h2>' +
		'<p>It’s Good to Give are a young local charity aiming to support children and young people with cancer. Their long term aim is to build a respite house for young people and their families and excitingly work has recently started on the construction. With our 2016 Christmas concert we managed to raise £284 to help with their work.</p>'],
       
        ["../Images/WaverleyCare.jpg",
        '<h2>Our Charities:  &nbsp;<a href="http://www.waverleycare.org/">Waverley Care</a></h2>'+
        '<p>In the run up to Christmas we’re big fans of sharing festive musical joy, and doing a bit of fundraising on the side! For several years we have raised money for Waverley Care who support people living with HIV and Hep C throughout Scotland.</p>'],
        
        ["../Images/TourGroup.jpg",
        '<h2>Our Charities: &nbsp;<a href="https://www.ijm.org/">International Justice Mission</a> and &nbsp;<a href="https://www.thebraintumourcharity.org/">the Brain Tumour Charity</a></h2>'+
        '<p>In January 2017 our third annual tour went north to Aberdeenshire. We had a fantastic time exploring this beautiful part of Scotland and eating enormous ice creams by the beach. We also put on two concerts in Banchory and Stonehaven, which were really well received and raised £470 for our two charities. The International Justice Mission is a global charity working to protect the world’s most vulnerable people from slavery and violence; the Brain Tumour Charity funds scientific research and supports patients and their families. </p>'],
        
        ["../Images/Charities1516.jpg",
        '<h2>Our Charities 2015-16</h2>'+
        '<b>Spring 2016 &nbsp;<a href="http://samaritans.org/your-community/samaritans-work-scotland">Samaritans of Edinburgh and the Lothians</a></b>'+
        '<p>With this concert we raised &pound;365 for our local branch of the Samaritans who give support to people who are struggling to cope, with the vision that fewer people will die by suicide. They provide 24 hour phone support, run workshops for children and young people, and support communities after a suicide</p>'+
        '<b>Lake District Tour</b>'+
        '<p>With our second Cumbrian Tour we held concerts in Maryport and Wigton, raising money for the local lifeboat service and for a church youth group. Our concerts came just after devastating floods hit the local communities where the lifeboat volunteers played a key part in evacuating people from their homes to safety. With both concerts, we were delighted to donate &pound;550 to these causes.</p>'+
        '<b>Christmas 2015 &nbsp;<a href="http://500miles.co.uk/">500 Miles</a></b>'+
        '<p>Our Christmas concert and ceilidh were a huge success raising &pound;640 for 500 Miles. This charity was founded by a local woman who lost her limbs, so that people in Sub-Saharan Africa could get the same quality of prosthetic limbs as she was able to benefit from here in the UK. The charity has made a huge difference to the lives of many people. </p>'],
        
        ["../Images/JurassicStarWars.jpg",
        '<h2>John Williams</h2>'+
        '<b>Spring Concert 2016</b>'+
        '<p><b>Highlights from Jurassic Park</b></p>'+
        '<p>The full film score from Jurassic Park contains a vast variety of themes ranging from the opening classic intended to "capture the awesome beauty and sublimity of the dinosaurs in nature" to "wild orchestral and choral things; the idea was to shake the floor and scare everybody".</p>'+
        '<b>Music from Star Wars</b>'+
        '<p>Arranged for String Ensemble by our own James Renwick, the Star Wars themes draw on an eclectic variety of musical styles that grew over the many films. On this evolution Williams reflects “it\'s a bit like adding paragraphs to a letter that\'s been going on for a number of years. It\'s an extension of something that\'s been really organic and continually growing."</p>'
        ]
    ]

    var infoIndex = getRandomInt(0, info.length);
    
    function loadInfo(index)
    {
        if (info.length == 0) return;

        var banner = document.getElementById("infobanner");
        var host   = document.getElementById("info_host");

        banner.style.backgroundImage = 'url(' + info[index][0] + ')';
        host.innerHTML               = info[index][1];
    }

    function infoLeft()
    {
        if (--infoIndex == -1) { 
            infoIndex = info.length - 1;
        }
        loadInfo(infoIndex)
    }
    function infoRight()
    {
        if (++infoIndex == info.length) { 
            infoIndex = 0;
        }
        loadInfo(infoIndex)
    }


    loadInfo(infoIndex)
</script>
@section infobanner {
<div id="infobanner">
    <div class="arrowL" onclick="infoLeft()"></div>
    <div class="arrowR" onclick="infoRight()"></div>
    <div id="info_host" class="overlay"></div>
</div>
}

